Text: Moodys Investors Service downgrads EnronMoodys Investors Service downgraded Enron Corps longterm debt by one notch this morning a move sure to hamper the companys efforts to restore investor and client confidence Shares of Enron fell to sevenyear lows this morning losing to trade at in midday trading In the past two weeks the stock has lost more than half its value dropping from as high as at the beginning of October Enrons rating was lowered by the bond rating firm from Baa to Baa where it will remain on review for further downgrade Moodys said in a statement The firm also placed the Houston companys Prime rating for commercial paper on review for downgrade The Baa rating is just two notches above what is commonly called junk bonds
